stylometry: The tradeoff managers must consider regarding waiting lines is having enough employees to serve all the customers in a timely matter while not having too many employees working because then it will be a waste of money to pay them to be there. The costs are the employees salaries and the lost business from customers waiting in line too long and leaving. The objective is to have the correct number of employees working in order to serve all the customers in a timely matter without having employees idle. In other words, the service rate needs to match (or match as closely as possible) with the arrival rate.
